0945017b-7272-4d03-ae9f-7c6eaf0b1bf7.2f30121b-27e1-4d6c-99b8-69232c337f27.description=
Checks to see if a string matches a specific rule.

Inputs\:
matchType - The type of match to perform.
toMatch - The string to check if matches another string.
matchTo - The string to match against.
ignoreCase - Boolean value for whether or not to ignore case during match.

Responses\:
success - The String matched.
failure - The string did not match, or something went wrong.
0945017b-7272-4d03-ae9f-7c6eaf0b1bf7.4a2b321e-e88d-4247-b44c-de962c8c4ee8.prompt=Enter a value for toMatch 0945017b-7272-4d03-ae9f-7c6eaf0b1bf7.4ca499b7-b71c-46f7-b61c-bf4e5925da65.description=
Adds a value into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the context variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the context variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];

If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. 0945017b-7272-4d03-ae9f-7c6eaf0b1bf7.847144cb-3b99-45f9-8303-b0bf52c47a98.description=

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the context variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the context variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
0945017b-7272-4d03-ae9f-7c6eaf0b1bf7.88f83772-21e8-456c-80e8-0c4a85b5991f.prompt=Delimiter\: 0945017b-7272-4d03-ae9f-7c6eaf0b1bf7.99b696d1-3053-4ad1-b4ed-368813def722.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);
0945017b-7272-4d03-ae9f-7c6eaf0b1bf7.c85e5a35-816c-4b4b-a589-2603288c538a.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified key is null. Inputs\: keyName - the key to check Returns\: The value in the specified key. Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer. notNull - if some value is stored in the key. 0945017b-7272-4d03-ae9f-7c6eaf0b1bf7.d4c72baf-877a-49d2-9881-715463fcee50.prompt=Type of Match to Perform\: 0945017b-7272-4d03-ae9f-7c6eaf0b1bf7.description=
Gets a list of one or more Elements in a list that match to the value specified in the input "compareTo" based on the input "matchType".  

Inputs\:
list - The list to search.
delimiter - The delimiter that separates elements in list.
compareTo - The string to compare each element in the list against.
matchType - The type of match to perform.

Responses\:
success - 1 or more elements were found that matched.
failure - no elements matched, or something went wrong.

Results\:
others -  A delimiter delimited list of elements that do not match
matches - A delimiter delimited list of elements that match the rule.
